cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.RO

The paper discusses optimization methods for deep reinforcement learning algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence research. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions empirical results on a subset of the classic ATARI 2600 games, indicating a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories.
